nl_problem:
# Task: Multi-Constraint Check (Density 2)
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: isValid(self, n: int) -> bool

# Objective:
Return True if the integer `n` satisfies ALL of the following 2 independent constraints:
1. n is greater than 2
2. n is not equal to 104
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "isValid")
  (signature ( (n int) ) bool)
  (constraints
    (constraint "n must be greater than 2")
    (constraint "n must not be equal to 104")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Return True if the integer `n` satisfies ALL of the following 2 independent constraints:")
    (rule "1. n is greater than 2")
    (rule "2. n is not equal to 104")
    (return "True if all constraints are satisfied, False otherwise.")
  ))
generated_code:
# solution.py
from typing import List, Optional, Dict, Set, Any
import heapq
import collections

# Define any helper classes here if needed

class Solution:
    def isValid(self, n: int) -> bool:
        # Check if n is greater than 2
        if n <= 2:
            return False
        
        # Check if n is not equal to 104
        if n == 104:
            return False
        
        # If both conditions are satisfied, return True
        return True
